group.label: CEE #: S\_01\_19 Data Quality Assurance (Routine Activities)

input.label: __*STANDARD: Each site follows routine data quality assurance (DQA) procedures to verify the accuracy and completeness of reported ailment program data on at least a quarterly basis.*__

select1.label: Does the site have a documented process or set of standard operating procedures to ensure that the data it collects and reports to stakeholders accurately reflect the services provided at the site?

select.label: Which of the following data quality assurance or review activities are completed at least quarterly at the site?
select.hint: Tick all that apply; Note: Routine data quality assurance activities may be conducted either by on-site staff, implementing partner staff, or an external team assigned to review the site.

item.label: Reviews of registers and/or client record systems for data completeness
Crosschecking (comparing) monthly reported results with client records, pharmacy records, registers, or other data sources
Categorizing and separating active or enrolled client records from inactive/LTFU clients for reporting accuracy and client follow-up
Assessing results during data review meetings with program staff; highlighting data discrepancies or outlier values; and documenting data quality concerns

group.label: CEE #: S\_01\_20 Assessment & Utilization of Performance Data in QI Activities

input.label: __*STANDARD: Each site has a process for routinely recording, reviewing, and using program data to inform implementation of quality improvement (QI) activities.*__

select1.label: Does the site review key programmatic/performance indicators at least quarterly over the last 12 months at a minimum?
select1.hint: Note: Programmatic/performance indicators can include PEPFAR Monitoring Evaluation and Reporting (MER) and/or Quality Improvement indicators. Documentation may include run charts, bar graphs, site reports, QI team improvement journals etc. If the site only reports annual review of key indicators, this response should be "No"

select1.label: Does a multidisciplinary team meet and discuss programmatic/performance data at least quarterly?
select1.hint: Note: Multidisciplinary team includes clinicians, program staff, M&E staff, lay counsellors, social workers, pharmacists, volunteers etc.

select1.label: Is there a documented site level plan for program improvement or QI initiatives outlining roles, responsibilities, activities implemented and quantifiable projected outcomes?

group.label: CEE #: S\_01\_21 Data Reporting Consistency – TX\_NEW-C&T

input.label: __*STANDARD: Indicator reports in TEST for PEPFAR Monitoring Evaluation Reporting (MER) indicator TX\_NEW match summary reports maintained at facility level for the same reporting period.*__

_Instructions: Does this facility report on the PEPFAR MER TX\_NEW indicator? If NO, check NA, and SKIP this CEE. If YES, assessor must retrieve the facility-level TEST indicator report for the last PEPFAR quarterly report prior to visit._

select1.label: For TX\_NEW, does the facility have the summary report (monthly or quarterly) or summary number for the exact same reporting period of the TEST report retrieved by the assessor?
select1.hint: (Note: A quarterly TEST report may need to be reconstructed from 3 monthly reports found at the facility.)

input.label: Using the TEST report and the facility summary report(s), fill in the table below
